        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/l/ccd318/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2024-12-01T13:59:27.127Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I have noticed, that if Signal reminds me of entering my password, I don’t need to press any button or enter if I’ve input the right password.</p>\n<p>Isn’t this a security threat? Couldn’t someone figure out the password by bruteforcing every single combination, until Signal accepts it?</p>",
