        "id": 256482,
        "name": "",
        "username": "Herohtar",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/herohtar/{size}/43780_2.png",
        "created_at": "2024-12-01T20:26:51.215Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"lajawi\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"65216\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/l/ccd318/48.png\" class=\"avatar\"> lajawi:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Isn’t this a security threat? Couldn’t someone figure out the password by bruteforcing every single combination, until Signal accepts it?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>No, it’s not a risk, because if someone has access to your phone and is able to see the password reminder, they can already access all your Signal data. If they wanted to, they could just go change your Signal password to something else.</p>",
