        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/l/ccd318/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2024-12-01T20:54:28.103Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote group-volunteer_moderators\" data-username=\"Herohtar\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"65216\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/herohtar/48/43780_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> Herohtar:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>No, it’s not a risk</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>So the behaviour of that password field is different when you actually need it to unlock whatever it is protecting? If so, then no, it is not a risk.</p>",
