        "id": 256491,
        "name": "",
        "username": "Herohtar",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/herohtar/{size}/43780_2.png",
        "created_at": "2024-12-01T21:06:13.334Z",
        "cooked": "<p>The password (“Signal PIN”) is used to restore your account on a new install/device and also doubles as the Registration Lock PIN. Both of those scenarios are heavily rate limited to prevent brute forcing. The reminder dialog isn’t meant to protect your account, so does not need any such protections; it is only to help you remember the PIN so that if you end up needing it to restore access to your account you don’t end up locking yourself out by trying a bunch of incorrect passwords.</p>",
